(Alright let’s try that again) 😅
What’s your fav game day appetizers?
I don’t game day often, but the one time I did I had this buffalo ranch dip, and it was AMAZIN. I had to make it myself this year bc delicious.
It was 10/10 with @myproteinus bbq protein chips. Definitely stock up for the next time you have some pals over or if you wanna snack AND get some protein in 😌 all snacks are 55% off rn through the link in my bio
•
Full disclosure, this recipe that I used had some errors in it, and it may be in your best interest to just use an oven!
So here in the caption I’m gonna share a revised version so I do not fail you all😅
•
RECIPE
1st step:
Cook 1.5 lbs of chicken breasts and shred them— either with two forks or a hand mixer.
Preheat oven to 350°

MIX ALL OF THE FOLLOWING INGREDIENTS IN A LARGE BOWL. 

Shredded chicken
8 oz of softened cream cheese (I used light/low fat cream cheese bc there’s enough fat in this recipe 😅)
1 pack of ranch dressing seasoning
1 cup of hot sauce
6 oz of shredded cheese (the recipe I used called for 16 oz and it was way too much)

BAKE 20 MINS

You can also put shredded cheese on top and broil for 3 mins to get the crispy layer over top :)

🎵 Music by @fijiblue — Butterflies via @hellothematic

This was my quick therapeutic stretchin and handstand session from this morning. Overall this was around 20 mins before I had to work on some things today.

Then I moved into some handstand work, some one armed handstands and press handstand drills. Not even close to being able to do a press handstand but I wanted to try it out! Definitely need to work on getting my core and form down on handstands, stretch, get a bit more flexible before moving on into press handstand work.

🥞🍫🍌 
•
I have been loving these protein pancakes... they’re legit so good, I eat them as a late night snack sometimes too 😅
Save this post for later to try it for yourself
•
Ingredients:
🍌 1/2 a banana
🥞 2 scoops of @myproteinus Protein Pancake Mix (45% off w my code- PINEAPPLE, Link in bio)
💦 3 TBSP of water
🥛 1/3 cup oatmilk 
🍫 Dark Chocolate chips
•
Add the Protein Pancake mix, 3 tbsp of water, and 1/3 cup of oatmilk into a mixing bowl. Combine until smooth. Slice banana into small pieces, then put a few into the mixture. Make sure the banana is covered by the batter, and spoon it out onto a pan on medium heat. Add your chocolate chips to the top. Flip after the bottom is golden! When both sides are golden, you’re done :-)
•
For a lower carb option, you can omit the banana, use water instead of oatmilk, or use stevia chocolate chips 👏🏻

After posting my before and after touching my toes on my story the other day, I received sooo many questions about what I do or how I improved, so I made this lil IGTV tutorial :)
•
Wearing @myproteinus Power Marl set in Crushed Berry 🍓🍇🍒 MP is holding a pre-labor day sale right now, and my code PINEAPPLE is 40% off btw 😏😏
•
(the before and after I show in the video is just for demonstrating where I was at and where I currently am at— I’ll post my ACTUAL progress in my story!)
Try out these stretches and hold each for at least 30 seconds each day. 
•
When I first began to stretch consistently, I used the stretching strap each night, and held the stretch on and off for around 10 minutes while watching a show or youtube. 
I try to stretch at least once daily, usually before bed and/or during/after my workouts. 
I honestly do the forward fold for around 30 mins while I diffuse my hair upside down every few days too 😆
•
Really all there is to it is not getting discouraged. I know it can be sooo discouraging just sitting and feeling like gravity can’t even help you do the work because you can’t even bend forward far enough! Slow and steady wins the race. I didn’t even realize how far I’d come and it has been a pretty short amount of time!

As lots of you know, I’ve been practicing handstands and other moves in order to gain upper body and core strength. It’s just a fun move I’m trying to accomplish, because it’s something I used to write off as “impossible” for myself to achieve.
•
🐜 Dead bugs— this is a great beginner workout, especially if you are unable to do the hollow body. I really struggled with ab strength in the beginning and would always find myself arching my back to compensate for my lack of ab strength.
🦵🏼Hollow body- I love this exercise. I think everyone should know about it, and should practice it, because it really targets a bulk of your body stabilization muscles. If you can’t put your legs down all the way, practice lowering your legs and holding them right before the point where your back lifts off the ground. 
🖐🏻Stretch and warm up wrists- Always always do this before going into handstand practice. You will be holding your entire body weight on your wrists and hands.
✔️Wall assisted L-shaped handstand- These really helped me with the idea of ‘opening my shoulders’. You can also use a box, table, or a couch to rest your feet on instead of the wall.
💪🏼Wall assisted handstand shoulder taps- I started doing this when I realized how difficult it was to lift my hands up for wall walk ups.
👣Wall walk ups- These are recommended by almost every handstand enthusiast I have come across. They help increase strength and will help with your endurance and balance in a handstand hold later on. 
🆙Wall assisted handstand hold- When I started focusing on my hands and shifting the weight between my palms and fingertips, that’s when I really started to notice my abs firing to save myself from falling over! Remember to switch the foot that you start off with in this movement so you don’t develop muscle imbalances (I skipped this step and I’m paying for it now!)
•
These are some exercises that I have researched myself, and have gotten from tons of professional handstand/gymnastics trainers online. I am not a professional when it comes to hand balancing, and I am just learning myself! Take my advice here and research it on your own to perfect your form 👍🏻
